From: Kuan-Ying Lee <kuan-ying.lee@mediatek.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] xfrm: Add packet fragmentation before hardware encryption

Add IP fragmentation support before hardware encryption for XFRM packet
offload mode.  When the hardware crypto accelerator cannot handle packet
fragmentation, perform ip_do_fragment() in xfrm_dev_offload_ok() before
sending packets to hardware.  Also add safety checks in xfrm_output_resume()
to handle fragmentation failures gracefully.

This fixes silent drops of oversized IKEv2 IKE_AUTH messages (common with
EAP-AKA/EAP-SIM for VoWiFi) when hardware packet offload is active, which
causes IKEv2 retransmit timeouts and slow VoWiFi connection establishment.

[dpawlik: ported from mtk-openwrt-feeds 25.12 999-crypto-05]
Signed-off-by: Daniel Pawlik <pawlik.dan@gmail.com>
---
 net/xfrm/xfrm_device.c |  6 ++++++
 net/xfrm/xfrm_output.c | 13 ++++++++++++-
 2 files changed, 19 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

--- a/net/xfrm/xfrm_device.c
+++ b/net/xfrm/xfrm_device.c
@@ -427,6 +427,12 @@ bool xfrm_dev_offload_ok(struct sk_buff
 			goto ok;
 	}

+	if (x->props.family == AF_INET && x->xso.type == XFRM_DEV_OFFLOAD_PACKET) {
+		skb_gso_reset(skb);
+		IPCB(skb)->frag_max_size = mtu;
+		if (!ip_do_fragment(dev_net(skb_dst(skb)->dev), skb->sk, skb, xfrm4_output))
+			return true;
+	}
 	return false;

 ok:
--- a/net/xfrm/xfrm_output.c
+++ b/net/xfrm/xfrm_output.c
@@ -583,7 +583,18 @@ out:

 int xfrm_output_resume(struct sock *sk, struct sk_buff *skb, int err)
 {
-	struct net *net = xs_net(skb_dst(skb)->xfrm);
+	struct dst_entry *dst = skb_dst(skb);
+	struct net *net = NULL;
+
+	/* If an IPsec tunnel is HW offloaded, all packets should be sent to EIP.
+	 * However, EIP cannot fragment packets, so we perform ip_do_fragment()
+	 * in xfrm_dev_offload_ok(). If ip_do_fragment() failed, the original skb
+	 * will reach here and needs to be returned.
+	 */
+	if (unlikely(!dst || !(dst->xfrm)))
+		return -EINVAL;
+
+	net = xs_net(dst->xfrm);

 	while (likely((err = xfrm_output_one(skb, err)) == 0)) {
 		nf_reset_ct(skb);
